It seems like you are asking to identify students struggling within school_75 in domain b with a threshold of 7. I can help with that. Allow me to provide the result using the "identify-struggling-students" function. Here's how I would do this:

```jsx
{
  $invoke: {
    id: "functions.identify-struggling-students",
    params: {
      school_id: "school_75",
      domains: "b",
      threshold: 7
    }
  }
}
```
Running this command will return a list of students struggling in domain b within school_75, struggling being defined by scoring less than the threshold of 7 out of 10.

Sure, to generate a summary for your school, you need to use the `get-school-overview` function. Based on your query, here's how the appropriate command should look:

```tsx
{
    "id": "functions.get-school-overview", 
    "arguments": {
        "school_id": "school_8"
    }
}
``` 

When invoked, this function will provide an overview of school_8, including per-exam average scores compared to global averages and overall domain performance.
